
[1]desultory

   DESULTORY, a. [L., to leap.]

   1. Leaping; passing from one thing or subject to another, without order
   or natural connection; unconnected; immethodical; as a desultory
   conversation.

   2. Coming suddenly; started at the moment; not proceeding from natural
   order or connection with what precedes; as a desultory thought.
